The paper deals with the problem of combining deep learning and classical planning to solve long-horizon tasks from raw sensory input. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with the problem of planning and acting in the real world, which is a core concern of both fields. The use of deep learning and graphical methods also suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.LG and cs.CV. Finally, the focus on long-horizon tasks and the use of memory structures suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.SY.
